## 2. Data Flow Lifecycle

### Phase A: Room Creation & Bot Spawning
1. Client requests `CREATE_PARTY` or `START_BOT_MATCH`.
2. Server instantiates room structure `rooms[code]`. If Bot Match is selected, server spawns $N$ AI bot objects into the array.

### Phase B: Waiting Room & Hunter Step Detection
1. Clients broadcast position data at $60\text{ Hz}$.
2. Server evaluates positions against the central Hunter Step bounding box:
   $$\text{IsStandingOnStep} = (X_{\text{min}} \le P_x \le X_{\text{max}}) \land (Z_{\text{min}} \le P_z \le Z_{\text{max}})$$
3. Timer hits 0 $\rightarrow$ Server assigns `role = 'Hunter'` to the step occupant and broadcasts `MATCH_START`.

### Phase C: Active Match Cycle (Painting & Transformation)
1. **Paint Event:** Client raycasts mouse coordinates against world geometry $\rightarrow$ derives Hex/RGB color $\rightarrow$ updates local UV texture $\rightarrow$ emits `PAINT_UPDATE` payload to room.
2. **Pose Event:** Client changes bone transforms $\rightarrow$ emits `POSE_UPDATE` payload.